Preheat your #oven{} to 180°. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and
seeds. Slice into thin strips. Pop the pepper and whole @baby plum tomatoes{250}
onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{} and sprinkle over a pinch
of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place on the top shelf of the oven to roast until the
pepper is soft and the tomatoes burst, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through
and lightly press the tomatoes with a #fork{} to help the juices escape!

While the tomatoes and peppers cook, fill a large #saucepan{} with water and
add a good pinch of @salt{}. Bring to the boil over high heat. Peel and grate
the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Finely chop
the @chives{1} and crumble the @feta cheese{100}.

When the water is boiling, add the @penne pasta{200} to the saucepan and cook
for ~{12%minutes}.

Pop the @baby spinach{125} into a #colander{}. When the wheat penne has finished
cooking, pour the wheat pasta it into the colander and leave to sit on top of
the spinach to wilt it. Drizzle with a little @olive oil{2} to stop it from
sticking together. Keep the pan!

After the veggies have been roasting for 25 mins, heat the @olive oil{} in the
now empty saucepan over medium heat. Once hot, stir in the garlic and
@tomato puree{30}. Stirring, cook for ~{30%seconds}, then mix in the
@balsamic vinegar{12} and @sugar{1/2}. Bubble for ~{1%minute} to evaporate the
vinegar. Remove the pan from the heat.

Once cooked, stir the roasted veggies, all their juices, the @Flora Original{10},
the chives and @?olives{30} (if everyone likes them!) into the sauce. Tip the
wheat pasta into the pan and gently toss to coat well in the sauce. Season to
taste with salt and pepper. Divide the wheat pasta between your #bowls{} and
top with the crumbled feta and a dollop of @green pesto{45}. Enjoy!

> Our penne pasta dish is packed full of heavenly flavour combinations. Sweet
and juicy roasted red pepper and baby plum tomatoes, salty olives, tangy feta,
and pesto come together to create a dish that isn't showy but instead claims the
limelight by being deliciously uncomplicated. Ready in six speedy steps, this
is a weeknight winner for sure.